3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses methods from the literature to provide formal guarantees on the distribution of instances, which can be seen as a problem in optimization and search, both of which are common topics in evolutionary computing. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with scheduling tasks on machines with heterogeneous execution costs, which can be seen as a problem in control and optimization of systems. 

5. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a method for generating cost matrices, which can be seen as a problem in designing programming languages and tools for optimization and decision-making.
